    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Recover incomplete checkouts with HTTP / REST API and Discord on autopilot\n\n**Pattern:** Abandoned Cart Recovery · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nRecover incomplete checkouts with HTTP / REST API and Discord on autopilot. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual inventory is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Read Pending Queue (Google Sheets) → Work in Batches → Aggregate Batch Results → Mark Completed in Google Sheets → Send Summary to Discord\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to abandoned cart recovery without manual effort\n- Anyone automating inventory in e-commerce\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Improves response time\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Discord webhook URL; Google OAuth2 / service account.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "81631e6c-e91a-cb73-f33f-86263bd33214",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
